Abia Warriors football club of Umuahia have moved to Nanka, Orumba North Local Government Area of Anambra State for a two-week closed camping exercise in preparation for the commencement of the 2018/2019 Nigeria Professional Football League,National Daily learnt.
The team comprising 36 players and 14 officials arrived Nanka for the closed camping exercise and has been training at the Neros SportsÂ  Stadium under the supervision of Head Coach, Adenrele Moses.
Addressing the players, Coach Moses reminded them of the need to remain focused and disciplined in order to achieve the aim of embarking on the exercise and justify the huge resources committed by management into the programme.
